<br>
From levels 49 to 55 the only time my xp was better groupin was when I was highest level in group or was grouped with very high level friends killin mobs I shouldnt have been anywhere near.  I did not have uber gear.  I have only gotten some of my nice upgrades these last 2 levels and I still need alot of work.  <br>
<br>
I found that Lguk was the best place from 49 to 55.  I also did Cyndrella and Sol B, never liked KC or DL.  Lguk always gave me the best xp.  Basicly in guk it was pull Kill 1 or 2 then Helm heal then rinse and repeat.  Used root if I got multiples hardly ever need to root heal the mob but when neccessary was able.  Rarely stun used mana for buffs.  <br>
<br>
The disparity of my xp between groupin and soling during 54 to now has me basicly sending all my group xp to aa and all my solo xp to leveling (sometimes put 10% into aa when I was close to geting a point).  <br>
<br>
Now some say I shouldnt put any xp into aa till I am level 60 but I disagree.  This is much more effcient use of my XP.  And having run 2 helps a great deal on those rare occasions when my encounters with AM and lord in LGuk go south on me.<br>
<br>
My point is in no way do you need uber gear as a paladin to solo effectively as a paladin.  Are we as effective as other hybrids and melees.  I honestly don't know.  What I do know is I am happy with my current abilites to solo.  If you are unhappy with your ability to solo then I would look at the suggestions that have been posted and try them.  If you are still unhappy then I would recommend you do not solo cause nothing will change your opinion.  <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=139732" target="_blank">Stillgar Argus</a> - 57 Paladin<BR>
Circle of Souls - Tarew Marr<BR>
<BR>

"The Secret to Immortality is to 
live a life WORTH remembering!"<BR>
